	<body>

		<div class="reveal">

			<!-- Any section element inside of this container is displayed as a slide -->
			<div class="slides">

				<section>
					<h2 style="text-align: justify;">Fixing Bugs on Open Sourced Projects</h2>
					<h4 style="text-align: left; text-transform: lowercase;">- by Jimmy Ngu</h4>
				</section>

				<section>

					<section>
						<h2>Bugs on Open Sourced Projects</h2>
					</section>

					<section>
						<img src="/images/rails_issues.png">
					</section>

					<section>
						<img src="/images/jekyll_issues_bugs.png">
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Bugs on Open Sourced Projects (cont.)</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Like any projects, there will be bugs</li>
							<li>Relies on community to report & fix bugs</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Why Help?</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Giving back</li>
							<li>Great Learning</li>
							<li>Recognition</li>
							<li>Great for resumes</li>
							<li>Learn to work with others remotely</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Which Project?</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Project you use the most <br />(e.g. Rails / Sinatra / Devise / Grape / Omniauth)</li>
							<li><a href="http://codetriage.com" target="codetriage">CodeTriage.com</a></li>
							<li>Github Trending / Explore</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Report Issues</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Go to Github Issues</li>
							<li>Check for existing reports</li>
							<li>Title & clear description</li>
							<li>Explain how to reproduce issue</li>
							<li>Code samples</li>
							<li>Write a failing test</li>
							<li>Be patient, wait, respond & discuss</li>
							<li>Don't expect someone to jump on it immediately</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Security Issue</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Don't just report it publicly</li>
							<li>Contact core developers</li>
							<li>Read guidelines</li>
							<li>Bounty Sites (e.g. <a href="https://hackerone.com/rails" target="hackerone">HackerOne</a>)</li>
							<li>Again .. wait for communication</li>
							<li>Don't cause bigger problems</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Help Solving Issues</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Help to verify bugs</li>
							<li>Contribute a failing test</li>
							<li>Submit a patch</li>
							<li>Testing patches</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>Submitting Patches</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Fork & install locally</li>
							<li>Write your code</li>
							<li>Make sure it actually works</li>
							<li>Write some tests</li>
							<li>Benchmark?</li>
							<li>Backport?</li>
						</ul>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h3>Demo Time !!</h3>
						<br />
						Audience Participation required 
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2>In the end ...</h2>
						<ul>
							<li>Open Source projects are powered by contributions</li>
							<li>It's fixed by someone spending time working on it</li>
							<li>And we are using it F.O.C</li>
							<li>If you really appreaciate someone solving your bug, send them some bitcoins to buy beer :D</li>
							<li><a href="https://rubytogether.org/" target="rubytogether">>> Ruby Together <<</a></li>
						</ul>
					</section>


				</section>

